will bring greater understanding of a group of reptiles that have existed for more than 160 million years, and that now inhabit every continent except Antarctica, as well as two of the great oceans. This volume pairs spectacular photos with easy-to-digest text. It is the first book on these creatures that combines a broad, worldwide sample with full-color, life-size accounts. Entries include close-ups of the snake’s head and a section of the snake at actual size. The detailed images allow readers to examine the intricate scale patterns and rainbow of colors as well as special features like a cobra’s hood or a rattlesnake’s rattle. The text is written for laypeople and includes a glossary of frequently used terms. Herpetologists and herpetoculturists alike will delight in this collection, and even those with a more cautious stance on snakes will find themselves drawn in by the wild diversity of the suborder Serpentes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSnakesvIdentification. 0aSnakesxIdentification. 0aSnakes. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh  areptiles, snakes, animals, animal lover, species, guidebook, handbook, life size, illustrated, pictures, photographs, worldwide, international, global, herpetology, herpetologist, zoology, zoologist, zoo, scary, pets, culture, cultural, fertility, birth, sin, death, symbolic, academic, scholarly, research, history, historical, full color, glossary, biology, biologist, serpentes, prey, hunting, reproduction, nature, natural world.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226459424423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226459424/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-all